<subSubSection id="D014DFD8FB5CAB1A9850E4A5AB9369D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="A861E2D4C31D46A76BFA0407A472331E" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B68EBB78C59A42061893EA2D29D03DD8" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="1828CC347ED3214592D056E6B3D5D3E9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male. Coloration</emphasis>
: Large body, yellowish-brown to dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AC5DCB60FE9F79146464A6AB21D6ABC5" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5A, B</figureCitation>
), face brown, ocelli milky (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="154A7F85A3C09F632F477FDE73255AE7" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5C</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palps brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BBBFFAB31F341A30F387A61662BA6966" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5E</figureCitation>
). The base of antenna yellowish brown, the rest dark brown. Pronotum yellowish-brown with posterior border black brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="221780DCE1BD46D771E0AC74DE59A2F9" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="27B5115E8CFCFA4E6E549065FD1FAC0B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Head</emphasis>
: Interocular distance obviously less than the distance between antennal sockets. Third segment of maxillary palps as long as the fifth segment, slightly longer than the fourth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9C4BA03B209BA92EE7795E52ECA253C8" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5E</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of pronotum obviously convex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A6FC67A1635DFC71903FE22047089642" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="12F15EC0770E962EFB5B0D8F67CAC40F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Tegmina and hindwings</emphasis>
: Both fully developed, extending beyond the end of abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8812CF1C9DAE2FE1F0A82EB6A008CEFE" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5H, I</figureCitation>
). Hind wings with RP bifurcated near the midpoint; the apex of M branched; CuA curved with 5-6 complete branches and 3 incomplete branches (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="13D235D0F55129F1561749529E8B4DD3" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="2B5A1A65578E1A7CEF0CE596FAFA6319" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Legs</emphasis>
: Front femur Type A3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7D80494E9876E7B1F63F6FA996D45579" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5F</figureCitation>
), pretarsal claws with pulvillus symmetrical and unspecialized. 
<emphasis id="804AEC171871802E3F80D3127222523A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Abdominal tergites</emphasis>
: Center of T1 ridged with a cluster of setae, T7 with a pair of obvious depressions and a tubercular process, where some bristles are present in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A2F24DD4FB7152301FEE55ADA50D84BE" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5G</figureCitation>
). T10 symmetrical, posterior margin slightly concave, and anterior margin with a cluster of setae. 
<emphasis id="72B0B6715F65388ED487D5FC6AC16829" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Paraprocts</emphasis>
: Dissimilar, the right one with a curved and spine-like process at base, left one with 3 spine-like processes of variable size (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDB2ABE79AD3B2C6802278E08D42FA99" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5J</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="750F1470E407E39D233383110D25437B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Subgenital plate</emphasis>
: Hind margin asymmetrical, left stylus arising at posterior margin with some spinules; right stylus crooked and irregular (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EBA12940C03C001320EF92E0934D70FD" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5N</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="950AE57141AD8EABFEA9AF221625AAA6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: L3 on the left side, of which the apex has an incision (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7552A10A6A7D15540B86A8491EEC9982" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5K</figureCitation>
); L2vm rod-like and with branches at apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C6E8D45B01C79A6087E5190247169080" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5L</figureCitation>
); R2, R3 made up of several sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D9F19429C771AB61B508EBEDD8D131EC" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Symploce tubercularis sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690405" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">5M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
