<subSubSection id="3CF44C2162D3420D01B96A730345EA69" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E633979D7DAA9ADA35503ABAE99281D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="723E090870B86829303A0D2D8578BEAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
The Latin word 
<emphasis id="05D01027D34347149792F1E3ABDD704E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">tubercularis</emphasis>
indicates T7 with a tubercular process in the middle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FFFF1FE4AA9B2AF1F3361C58F46B61A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="424A23EC9F7F4EFBC4B2AC30DB353266" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4012CB6CFA4DC8987AA696376FCCDE5" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="AD71D781B69B4E0CB1FADEC55559CF26" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce tubercularis" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tubercularis">
<emphasis id="499209F1F95B2C29F1D778D718E14766" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce tubercularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jin and Che 
<emphasis id="8BE7FFF2DAAB5861AD5E1D8FD79918FD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">sp. nov.</emphasis>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="9D41EBCADFEDF37A3538C7F04831FACB" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li, Liu, Qiu and Yue" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce maxima" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="3A3F78022F9631C39378D51BD5366899" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8DF60FFAB7472CD82FF6C42B401B4172" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.954.49738" author="Li, TT" journalOrPublisher="Zookeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="31 - 46" refId="B28" refString="Li, TT, Liu, DX, Qiu, DY, Yue, QY, 2020. Two new species of Episymploce Bey-Bienko, 1950 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) from China. Zookeys 954: 31 - 46, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.954.49738" title="Two new species of Episymploce Bey-Bienko, 1950 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) from China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.954.49738" volume="954" year="2020">Li et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) 
<emphasis id="0BF21505953D943F381D35FF982AE28F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">comb. nov.</emphasis>
, however, they can be distinguished by the following characteristics: 1) the former with a tubercular process in the middle of T7 that is absent in the latter; 2) the former with the right stylus crooked and irregular, while the latter has two small and simple styli; 3) the former with a setal tuft on supra-anal plate, but the latter without.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
